<br>
I do not expect that by throwing weight I will tip your scales. I do not expect to have much effect on your decision, as it is yours alone to make. I only want to speak briefly in favour of Obon, who has my Respect and Confidence.<br>
<br>
Guardians and Amazons have always been very close/similar in spirit... and any Dragon that has spent time with Us (I know who you are!) I genuinely believe can say that we do have some similarities with You as well.<br>
<br>
On that note... Something that I recently addressed in a post in our Officers' Lounge (forum) was my personal pet-peeve &quot;Alliance/ally&quot; distinction. Yes, they are essentially the same word, but I see an Alliance (upper-case A) with another guild as a commitment to a close relationship, almost a merger (something that makes me cringe)... whereas I feel that having another guild as an ally (lower-case a) means that you are friendly with each other and give the benefit of the doubt (until proven otherwise at which time you may want to re-evaluate), make an effort to Do Things Together (raid, group, party, chat, whatever), and provide help to each other if and when comfortably possible. *grin* I suppose this could be a female rationale for the difference between being &quot;in a serious Relationship&quot; and being &quot;just friends&quot; but I can't help it.<br>
<!--EZCODE EMOTICON START ;) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/wink.gif ALT=";)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
Anyway... all this Uli-babble is my way of saying that, as a duly-chosen (by me) representative of Guardians, I would like to extend our hand in Friendship to Dragon's Kin. We would be honoured to call you an ally against all the Icky-Bad-Awful Stuff out there in the Lands of EQ, and in doing so only ask that you think of Guardians as comrades as well.<br>
<br>
We are currently very strong in the 20-45 range, and therefore aren't a whole lot of help as far as Raids, etc. but we are able to offer support to those Kin that are alternates/lower in level... and as we grow up more we'll have more to offer our Friends.<br>
<br>
/full-tilt babble off<br>
<br>
<br>
Thank you for your space and time,<br>
<br>
~Uliana Vaena, Paladin of Tunare<br>
